lead_paragraph: FROM RIO JANEIRO.--By the arrival at Providence, of the schooner A. J. Hobart, Capt. GIVEN, we have advices from Rio Janeiro to the 19th of August. The United States ships Jamestown and Susquehannah; were in port. The former arrived' on the 15th, and the latter was undergoing repairs.
